@BretDevereaux This would require academia to not be built from the ground up on massive scale employer time theft. 

When I was a grad student, I was working a summer on a 20 hrs/wk contract for no academic credits on a non dissertation project. For all legal purposes I was a pure employee...

@cwjones89 @KKriegeBlog That said, I find conferences, being run by tenured or tenure-line faculty with salaries anywhere from 65-140k relying on unpaid graduate student labor 'for the CV lines' appalling, given the job market being what it is.

It's exploitation and deserves to be scorned for that.
